d-tuned trade-offs between competing regularizers and provides theoretical guarantees on generalization via manifold concentration inequalities. We expect AMR to significantly outperform existing methods in low-data regimes (<10 labels per annotator), improve calibration of aggregated predictions, and enable better detection of adversarial or inattentive annotators through geodesic outlier analysis.",
